cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves dynamically predicting weights for upscale filters, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
